</ul><h2 id="23december1998">Update 1408G # Date 23 December 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 5 - Age Pension - Chapter 5 - Department of Veterans Affairs payments. See guidelines 5.2000 to 5.2308.</p>
<p>A new section of the chapter is added on payment of age pension to veterans receiving Department of Veterans' Affairs disability pension. Minor changes are also made to chapter 5.</p>
<h2 id="15december1998">Update 1407G # Date 15 December 1998</h2>
<p>Topic 3.2.1.30 - Waiting Periods for NSA - Correction of policy relating to start date of 26 week waiting period for Customers from New Zealand.</p>
<p>Chapter 3.1 - General Provisions - Corrections to information about residence requirements and waiting periods for newly arrived residents.</p>
<h2>Update 1406G # Date 15 December 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 36 - Member of a Couple - Chapter 36 - Discretion not to treat customer as a member of a couple. See guidelines 36.500 to 36.534.</p>
<p>Section 24 may be applied where the person's partner is not residentially qualified or is subject to the newly arrived resident's waiting period (NARWP), and the person is in financial hardship. In brief, section 24 may be applied in such cases if the amount payable to the person at the partnered rate plus the couple's own income is less than the maximum rate payable to the couple if both were qualified for an income support.</p>
<h2 id="3december1998">Update 1405G # Date 3 December 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 47 - Drought Relief Payment - Chapter 47 has been made obsolete by the Farmer Assistance Scheme Library.</p>
<p>Chapter 47 has been replaced by Farmer Assistance Schemes Library which can be found in Centrelink Reference Suite under F in the alpha index. Drought Relief Payment has been replaced with Exceptional Circumstances Relief Payment (ECRP) which can be found in the Farmer Assistance Scheme library.</p>
<h2>Update 1404G # Date 3 December 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 5A - Retirement Assistance For Farmers - New Chapter 5A and new subsection 5A.1750. See guidelines 5A.000 to 5A.3101.</p>
<p>Introduction of RAFS allows older low income farmers to gift their farm without affecting their access to the age pension.</p>
<p>New subsection 5A.1750 - Eligible Termination Payment.</p>
<h2>Update 1403G # Date 3 December 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 11 - WIDOW B PENSION -. See guidelines 11.000 to 11.3106.</p>
<ul><li>Widow B pensioners paid under an international agreement who become eligible for an autonomous pension should be granted an autonomous pension.</li>
<li>Widow B pensioners overseas or paid under an international agreement or in receipt of ongoing compensation payments must not be transferred to age pension.</li>
</ul><h2 id="11november1998">Update 1402G # Date 11 November 1998</h2>
<p>This amendment incorporates extensive changes to Guide chapters as a result of the Guide Rewrite Stage 1.</p>
<p>Chapters amended have had text removed. The information is now contained in the appropriate sections of the Guide Rewrite. Where text has been removed you will find linked references to the Guide Rewrite.</p>
<p>Chapters affected are:</p>
<p>Chapter 2</p>
<p>Chapter 5A</p>
<p>Chapter 6</p>
<p>Chapter 8</p>
<p>Chapter 12</p>
<p>Chapter 14</p>
<p>Chapter 15</p>
<p>Chapter 17</p>
<p>Chapter 18N</p>
<p>Chapter 19</p>
<p>Chapter 20</p>
<p>Chapter 21</p>
<p>Chapter 23</p>
<p>Chapter 25</p>
<p>Chapter 26</p>
<p>Chapter 34</p>
<p>Chapter 35</p>
<p>Chapter 42</p>
<p>Chapter 48</p>
<p>Chapter 49</p>
<p>Chapter 50</p>
<h2 id="28october1998">Update 1401G # Date 28 October 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 31 - INCOME AND ASSETS - BUSINESS STRUCTURES AND TRUSTS - Income test treatment of offsetting losses between different business activities. See guidelines 31.1220 to 31.2121.</p>
<p>Offsetting losses from business activities must now be necessarily related to the business income being reduced.</p>
<h2>Update 1400G # 28 October 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 27 - INCOME OVERVIEW AND ASSESSMENT - Assessment of private annuities under the income test. See guideline 27.11400 to 27.12100.</p>
<p>Amendments to assessment of private annuities under the income test guidelines.</p>
<h2>Update 1399G # Date 28 October 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 28 - ASSETS - OVERVIEW AND ASSESSMENT - Notional ordinary income - property owned with separated partner. See guidelines 28.5750 to 28.5756.</p>
<p>Notional income under the hardship provisions where property is owned with a separated partner and people may be fleeing domestic violence.</p>
<h2>Update 1398G # Date 28 October 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 28 - ASSETS - OVERVIEW AND ASSESSMENT - Unreasonable assets - unable to sell. See guidelines 28.5500 to 28.5505.</p>
<p>Hardship rules, unrealisable asset, unable to sell property where a person flees the family home as a result of domestic violence.</p>
<h2>Update 1397G # Date 28 October 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 28 - ASSETS - OVERVIEW AND ASSESSMENT - See guidelines 28.7000 to 28.7601.</p>
<p>Assessment of private annuities under the assets test.</p>
<h2 id="21october1998">Update 1396G # Date 21 October 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 1 - GENERAL PROCEDURES inc TAX FILE NUMBER EXEMPTIONS - See guidelines 1.10000 to 1.10601.</p>
<p>Section on newly arrived resident's waiting period has been re-written to remove errors and provide better structured assistance to decision makers. In particular, the information on who has to serve a waiting period, and who is exempt, has been improved.</p>
<h2>Update 1395G # Date 21 October 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 33 - INCOME AND ASSETS - SUPERANNUATION FUNDS - Guidelines 33.3342 to 33.6360 have been deleted.</p>
<p>Guidelines 33.3342 to 33.6360 have been deleted.</p>
<h2 id="23september1998">Update 1394G # Date 23 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 33A - INCOME AND ASSETS - INCOME STREAMS - New Chapter. See guidelines 33A.000 to 33A.7052.</p>
<p>Addition of new chapter 33A.</p>
<h2>Update 1393G # Date 23 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 5 - AGE PENSION - Pension Bonus Scheme. See guidelines 5.2000 to 5.2610.</p>
<p>The pension bonus scheme commenced from 1 July 1998. It allows people of age pension age to defer their age pension whilst they continue to satisfy the work test requirements. At the time of claiming age pension they may qualify for a one-off tax-free lump-sum pension bonus equivalent to 9.4% of their annual pension for each year they have deferred.</p>
<h2>Update 1392G # Date 23 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 17 - FAMILY ALLOWANCE. See guidelines 17.9810 to 17.9811.</p>
<p>Revised list of Ministers of Religion who are not employees of their religious organisations.</p>
<h2>Update 1391G # Date 23 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENTS - Portability conditions for payment while outside Australia. See guidelines 42.150 to 42.158.</p>
<p>Exercise of discretionary powers with regard to continuation of benefits in cases where a departure certificate is not obtained.</p>
<h2>Update 1390G # Date 23 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 8 - CARER PAYMENT. Complete rewrite of Chapter 8. See guidelines 8.000 to 8.6801.</p>
<p>The chapter has been updated to reflect the changes in legislation effective from 1 July 1998 regarding the extension of qualification for carer payment for a profoundly disabled child and two or more disabled children. It has also been substantially restructured and renumbered with a number of minor amendments intended to clarify existing policy.</p>
<h2 id="9september1998">Update 1389G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 37 - COMPENSATION RECOVERY. Compensation Recovery - treatment of former Austudy recipients who have received lump sums prior to 30/6/98. See guideline 37.1200.</p>
<p>Clarifies the treatment of former Austudy customers who have transferred to youth allowance or Austudy payment and have received lump sum compensation payments prior to 30 June 1998.</p>
<h2>Update 1388G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT. See guidelines 15.4000 to 15.4010.</p>
<p>To insert a reference to a DOC (document created in the On-line Document recording System).</p>
<h2>Update 1387G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT. See guidelines 15.3510 to 15.3515.</p>
<p>To clarify a reference to the assets test in case of disaster.</p>
<h2>Update 1386G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT. See guidelines 15.3300 to 15.3308.</p>
<p>Add a reference to a new category of special benefit.</p>
<h2>Update 1385G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT. See guidelines 15.3040 to 15.3043.</p>
<p>Add a reference to a new category of special benefit.</p>
<h2>Update 1384G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT. See guidelines 15.2300 to 15.2306.</p>
<p>Add information about a new category of special benefit.</p>
<h2>Update 1383G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT. See guidelines 15.2100 to 15.2110.</p>
<p>Remove references to special benefit being payable under Austudy payment conditions.</p>
<h2>Update 1382G # Date 9 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT. See guidelines 15.000 to 15.008.</p>
<p>Additional information on special benefit new claim procedures.</p>
<h2 id="3september1998">Update 1374G # Date 3 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 37 - COMPENSATION RECOVERY - Compensation Recovery - Clarification of payments affected by the Compensation provisions. See guidelines 37.5200 to 37.5203.</p>
<p>Clarifies the treatment of arrears of periodic compensation payments, when the lump sum represents different payment periods paid at different rates.</p>
<h2>Update 1373G # Date 3 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 37 - COMPENSATION RECOVERY - (1) Compensation Recovery - Clarification of payments affected by the Compensation provisions.</p>
<p>(2) Compensation Recovery - Clarification of payments excluded from Compensation provisions. See guidelines 37.1000 to 37.1100.</p>
<p>(1) Clarifies the definition of compensation to include most payments made under income protection and accident insurance policies with the exclusion of those payments specifically mentioned in guideline 37.1100.</p>
<p>(2) Clarifies the exclusion from the definition of compensation applying income protection policies where the recipient has personally contributed to the policy and where no offset clause exists.</p>
<h2 id="2september1998">Update 1381G # Date 2 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 24 - BEREAVEMENT PAYMENTS. See guidelines 24.000 to 24.7541.</p>
<p>Amendment of directions on bereavement payment re notification requirements and war widows with DSS partners.</p>
<h2>Update 1380G # Date 2 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 32 - INCOME AND ASSETS - DEPRIVATION - Beneficiary of a Deceased Estate. See guidelines 32.2300 to 32.2303.</p>
<p>Deprivation provisions should be applied to a beneficiary who waives their right to an interest in a deceased estate.</p>
<h2>Update 1379G # Date 2 September 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 42 - PORTABILITY AND COMPARABLE FOREIGN PAYMENT - Verifying arrival in, and departure from Australia dates for Australian Passport holders. See guidelines 42.400 to 42.425.</p>
<p>From 11 July 1998 Australian passports have not necessarily been stamped with 'Arrival into or Departure from Australia' stamps. Verification of dates of arrival or dates of departure after 11 July 1998 can be obtained by sighting other travel documents held by customers or from the Department of Immigration and Multicultural Affairs, International Movement Records Unit by telephone (see Reference Update CB980104) or via completion of the 'Verification of Arrival into or Departure from Australia' Form.</p>
