<h2>Update 1368G # Date 19 August 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 23 - ADDITIONAL PAYMENTS - RENT ASSISTANCE, PHARMACEUTICAL ALLOWANCE, TELEPHONE ALLOWANCE, REMOTE AREA ALLOWANCE - Customers who sub-let in public housing. See guidelines 23.1950 to 23.1951.</p>
<p>From 1 January 1998 customers who sub-let in public housing are ineligible to receive rent assistance unless:</p>
<ul><li>the primary tenant pays market rent; or</li>
<li>the primary tenant has advised the state housing authority that they have a sub-tenant and the sub-tenants income has been taken into account when setting the rent payable.</li>
