<h2>Update 1329G # Date 8 July 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 37 - COMPENSATION RECOVERY - (1) Effect of Cunneen decision on lump sum payments. See guidelines 37.5000 to 37.5001. (2)Various amendments. See guidelines 37.5200 to 37.7402.</p>
<p>(1)Updates the Guide to reflect the decision of the Federal Court in Cunneen decision, that lump sum payments cannot be dissected into their component parts, even when arrears or advances of periodic payments are included in the lump sum.</p>
<p>(2) i) Clarify treatment of partners when periodic payments are received. ii) Clarify treatment of arrears of periodic payments. iii) Ensure legislation is followed when calculating preclusion periods. iv) Ensure part commutations of periodic payments are described. v) Ensure notional parenting payment (allowance) is deducted from charges in pre 20/3/97 settlements. vi) Ensure that lump sum payments are included in the assets test for partner of the compensation recipient.</p>
<h2>Update 1328G # Date 8 July 1998</h2>
