<h2>Update 1312G # Date 24 June 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 2 - METHODS OF PAYMENT AND TAXATION - Lump sum arrears for U18 youth allowance customers and taxable and non-taxable payments. See guidelines 2.7700 to 2.8003.</p>
<p>Youth allowance for U18s will generally be directed to parents, however, customers who receive youth allowance directly because they are homeless or live away from home will be vulnerable to lump sum payment problems. Identification of youth allowance, AUSTUDY payment etc as taxable or non-taxable payments.</p>
