<p>Youth allowance replaces additional family payment for O16s and AUSTUDY for U25s. Rate of DRP calculation will no longer include students 16-24.</p>
<p>Update 1301G # Date 24 June 1998</p>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Claimant disqualified for youth allowance due to industrial action. See guidelines 15.3700 to 15.3703.</p>
<p>Youth allowance replaces NSA for U21s and needed to be included as a payment type which disqualifies the claimant due to industrial action, as does NSA.</p>
<h2>Update 1300G # Date 24 June 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Abolition of Education Leaver Waiting Period. See guidelines 15.3200 to 15.3204.</p>
<p>Abolition of education leaver waiting period for all payments means that SpB will no longer be required for education leavers.</p>
<p>Update 1299G # Date 24 June 1998</p>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Rate payable for Australian citizen child of non-permanent resident not to exceed 'at home' rate of youth allowance. See guidelines 15.3040 to 15.3043.</p>
<p>YTA replaced by youth allowance from 1 July. Maximum rate payable changes from 'at home' rate of YTA to 'at home' rate of YA.</p>
<p>Update 1298G # Date 24 June 1998</p>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Increase in age for homeless students from 16 to 18. See guidelines 15.3010 to 15.3013.</p>
<p>The maximum age for SpB for homeless students has been increased to 18 years because of youth allowance requirement to be in education.</p>
<p>Update 1297G # Date 24 June 1998</p>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Youth allowance payable on prison release to qualified customers. See guidelines 15.2800 to 15.2921.</p>
<p>Insertion of reference to youth allowance as a payment which released prisoners U21 will qualify for the age for homeless full-time students increased from 16 to 18 because youth allowance will require young people to remain in education to 18.</p>
<h2>Update 1296G # Date 24 June 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Youth allowance available and most cases for expectant mothers. See guidelines 15.2600 to 15.2705.</p>
<p>With introduction of youth allowance, exemption from activity test allows expectant mothers to remain on youth allowance as with NSA. Removal of reference to YTA, which has been replaced by youth allowance.</p>
<p>Update 1295G # Date 24 June 1998</p>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Rate of special benefit not to exceed rate of NSA, YA or AUSTUDY payment. See guidelines 15.1000 to 15.1007.</p>
<p>Youth allowance replaces NSA for U21s. Insertion of youth allowance and AUSTUDY payment as limitations on rates for relevant customers.</p>
<p>Update 1294G # Date 24 June 1998</p>
<p>Chapter 15 - SPECIAL BENEFIT - Removal of AUSTUDY as a payment type. See guidelines 15.200 to 15.503.</p>
<p>AUSTUDY has been replaced by youth allowance and DSS AUSTUDY payment from 1 July. Removal of references to AUSTUDY.</p>
<h2>Update 1293G # Date 24 June 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 14 - SICKNESS ALLOWANCE - Abolition of Education Leaver Waiting Period. Guidelines 14.2770 to 14.2801 have been deleted.</p>
<p>The Education Leavers Waiting Period has been abolished for all payments.</p>
<h2>Update 1292G # Date 24 June 1998</h2>
