<h2>Update 1265G # Date 24 June 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 12 - NEWSTART - Changes to treatment of Community Development Employment Projects (CDEP). See guidelines 12.280 to 12.315.</p>
<p>Policy changes to CDEP stress that CDEP is voluntary: a person enters a CDEP scheme by their own choice. However, once a person signs up for the funding quarter they are generally expected to remain in the scheme. If they leave during a funding quarter their reason for leaving should be examined. These guidelines clarify when a person can leave the scheme without incurring a breach.</p>
