<h2 id="28may1998">Update 1249G # Date 28 May 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 17 - FAMILY ALLOWANCE - Change of care - child at risk of harm. See guidelines 17.4380 to 17.4385.</p>
<p>Sometimes children, especially in the older age groups, may reside with adults who are providing care for the child on an informal basis. These guidelines provide principles for dealing with family allowance claims in respect of children. Cases where there may be a significant risk of harm are to be referred to social work, who will provide a recommendation on the claim.</p>
<h2>Update 1248G # Date 28 May 1998</h2>
