<h2>Update 1247G # Date 28 May 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 28 - ASSETS - OVERVIEW AND ASSESSMENT - Application of the assets test to conventional life insurance policies. See guidelines 28.3100 to 28.3102.</p>
<p>These changes clarify that the surrender value of a conventional life insurance policy is clearly the asset of the policy holder or owner, or the person who has access to the value of the policy. The surrender value of such policies are not necessarily the asset of the beneficiary, or the life insured, unless they are also either the policy owner or the person who has access to the value of the policy.</p>
