<h2 id="30april1998">Update 1235G # Date 30 April 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 30 - INCOME: ASSESSMENT FROM FINANCIAL ASSETS - Assessment of superannuation guarantee charge contributions to superannuation funds after age pension age. See guidelines 30.4630 to 40.3632.</p>
<p>Superannuation guarantee charge (SGC) contributions to a customers' superannuation funds by employers are now mandatary where the employee is under age 70. Such contributions were mandatory up to age 65. SGC contributions are not assess as income for social security purposes where the customer is under age 70.</p>
