<h2 id="1march1998">Update 1151G # Date 1 March 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 27 - INCOME - OVERVIEW AND ASSESSMENT - Exchange rates. See guidelines 27.5000 to 27.6304.</p>
<p>(1) From 1 March 1998 exchange rates for all overseas currencies will be updated and applied monthly to customers' overseas income. They are no longer special arrangements for UK pensions.</p>
<p>(2) From 1 March 1998 there will be new arrangements in place to value customers' overseas income in Australian dollars for social security payment assessment purposes.</p>
<p>(3) From 1 March 1998 the exchange rate arrangements will change. From that date exchange rates for all overseas income will be updated automatically and applied to customers overseas income and assets records monthly.</p>
