<h2>Update 1123G # Date 15 January 1998</h2>
<p>Chapter 20 - MOBILITY ALLOWANCE - Issuing Form MA2 to customers. See guidelines 20.400 to 20.402.</p>
<p>A Mobility allowance - Medical Report (Form MA2) is not required in all cases to assess the level of a customer's disability in using public transport. Where a customers disability eg permanent blindness clearly indicates that they require substantial assistance to use public transport then the issue of a form Form MA2 is not required. The available medical information should be accepted as evidence that the customer is unable to use public transport without assistance.</p>
<h2>Update 1122G # Date 15 January 1998</h2>
